{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "URL Pattern Validation Hook",
  "description": "Validates that all URL references in templates exist in urls.py to prevent NoReverseMatch errors",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      "verifast_app/templates/**/*.html",
      "verifast_app/urls.py"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Template or URL configuration modified. Please validate URL consistency:\n\n1. **Extract URL References**: Find all `{% url 'app:name' %}` and HTMX endpoint references\n2. **Verify Existence**: Check each URL exists in verifast_app/urls.py\n3. **Test Resolution**: Run `python manage.py show_urls` to verify patterns\n4. **Check Parameters**: Ensure URL parameter patterns match view signatures\n\nFocus on critical URLs: speed_reader_init, speed_reader_complete, quiz_start, add_comment. Report missing patterns and suggest fixes."
  }
}